# Build-context exclusions for the live-scoring sandbox image.
#
# The current Dockerfile uses only multi-stage `COPY --from=` (no copy
# from the build context), so this file is forward-looking: any future
# Dockerfile change that introduces `COPY <ctx> ...` benefits from these
# exclusions. The sentinel below also acts as a regression probe — if
# `.dockerignore` ever stops being read by the builder, the sentinel
# will leak into the context and a follow-up audit can catch it.
#
# Verification per the U3-followup plan: build with `--progress=plain`
# and observe the "transferring context" line. The byte count should
# omit the sentinel + any matched glob below.

# Sentinel: must always be excluded from the context. Do not remove.
.ignored-sentinel.txt

# Standard housekeeping — even if nothing in the Dockerfile copies them
# yet, future contributors should not accidentally bake editor state or
# OS junk into a layer.
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
.vscode/
.idea/
